  "prompt": "Does NASA recruit Indians?",
  "response": "Yes, NASA does have opportunities for non-US citizens, including Indians, under certain programs and collaborations. While most positions at NASA generally require U.S. citizenship due to security and policy reasons, there are some exceptions where international participation is possible, particularly through partnerships with other space agencies like ISRO (Indian Space Research Organisation) or international science collaborations.\n\nAdditionally, NASA offers internships and research opportunities that may also be available to non-US citizens, depending on specific agreements and programs. Aspiring individuals from India often pursue educational and professional pathways that align with NASA's mission, and partnerships and collaborations between NASA and international entities can pave the way for Indian scientists, engineers, and researchers to work on NASA-related projects.",
